there's the real world.

00:33:28.630 --> 00:33:30.580
There are people
walking on the street,

00:33:30.580 --> 00:33:33.038
and they're looking at their
iPhones, and they're chatting.

00:33:33.038 --> 00:33:37.240
And I'm like, do they
think about these things?

00:33:37.240 --> 00:33:39.520
And so over these
years, and also because

00:33:39.520 --> 00:33:41.260
of a previous
career in Hollywood,

00:33:41.260 --> 00:33:45.460
being kind of on the other
side of things in storytelling,

00:33:45.460 --> 00:33:48.610
it kind of dawned on me over
time that what you really need

00:33:48.610 --> 00:33:52.611
is storytelling on a very
emotional, very emotive level,

00:33:52.611 --> 00:33:53.110
right?

00:33:53.110 --> 00:33:53.900
TODD PAGLIA: Yeah.

00:33:53.900 --> 00:33:55.483
